### 1. Create a valid job (expect 201)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/jobs
Content-Type: application/json

{"description":"Deliver package to downtown","pickupAddress":"123 Warehouse St","deliveryAddress":"456 Main St","scheduledAt":"2027-06-01T09:00:00"}

### 2. Create job with missing fields (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/jobs
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 3. Get all jobs (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/jobs

### 4. Get job by ID (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/1

### 5. Get job by non-existent ID (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/9999

### 6. Assign job to driver (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/1/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{"driverId":1}

### 7. Assign job to a busy driver (expect 409)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/2/assign
Content-Type: application/json

{"driverId":2}

### 8. Update job status - legal transition (expect 200)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{"newStatus":"IN_PROGRESS"}

### 9. Update job status - illegal transition (expect 422)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/jobs/1/status
Content-Type: application/json

{"newStatus":"UNASSIGNED"}

### 10. Get all drivers (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/drivers

### 11. Get drivers filtered by status (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/drivers?status=AVAILABLE

### 12. Get driver by ID (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/drivers/1

### 13. Get driver by non-existent ID (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/drivers/9999

### 14. Get driver job schedule by date (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/drivers/1/jobs?date=2027-06-01
